<BaseLayout title="Building" lang={locale} description="What Pablo Pastrana Vega is currently building and has built.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Building</h1>

    <h2>Now</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Dapper</strong> — CPO. Compliance infrastructure for regulated industries. We build tools that help organizations meet regulatory requirements without replacing the workflows they already depend on. 2023–present.
    </p>

    <div class="divider my-8" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <h2>Before</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Footwear company</strong> — Co-founded a direct-to-consumer footwear brand. Handled operations, supply chain, and the parts of building a physical product that no one warns you about. The experience shaped how I think about constraints — the kind you can't abstract away with software.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>University research</strong> — Worked at the intersection of anthropology and computer science, studying how institutions adopt (and resist) technology. This is where the thesis work on cross-sector incentive structures began.
    </p>

    <div class="divider my-8" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <h2>Side projects</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Buenaventura internet safety project</strong> — Organized the <em>Primer Conversatorio sobre el Uso Responsable del Internet</em> in Buenaventura, Colombia. A case study in what happens when you bring technology conversations to communities that are usually excluded from them. <a href="/en/buenaventura/">Read the full case study</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>This site</strong> — Built with Astro, Tailwind, and MDX. Bilingual. No templates, no CMS. <a href="https://github.com/pablopastranavega/personal-website" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Source on GitHub</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
